						<font class="section_heading">Saint Louis-Sports</font>
						<br />
						<br />
						St. Louis has enjoyed a rich tradition of professional sports. It is home to the St. Louis Cardinals, Rams, and Blues.
						<br />
						<br />
						The Cardinals play their home games at Busch Stadium which was built in 2006. The Cardinals started their inaugural season in their new stadium as World Series Champions.
						<br />
						<br />
						The Rams are St. Louis' second NFL team and have appeared in two Super Bowls since coming to St. Louis, winning Super Bowl XXXIV in 2000 under head coach Dick Vermeil.
						<br />
						<br />
						St. Louis was awarded an NHL franchise in 1967. Named the St. Louis Blues, they play their home games at the Scotttrade Center in downtown St. Louis.
